classes.name: Client
classes.description: Client class, starting point for interacting with the wrapper. As a general rule, there should only be one instance of Client in use.

methods.name: getPlayer
methods.description: Allows you to get statistics of player
examples: // { guild: true } - fetch player's guildhypixel.getPlayer('StavZDev', { guild: true }).then(player => {  console.log(player.level); // 141  console.log(player.rank); // 'MVP+'  console.log(player.guild); // null (player is not in guild)}).catch(e => {  console.log(e);})

Player online status.

Players can disable this endpoint via in-game settings. When done so the API will return as if the player is offline.

props.name: noAuctions

props.name: raw
props.description: If true, result will not contain parsed auctions, but will present them as it is received. This can speed up performance in some cases.

props.name: retries
props.description: Number of times to retry fetching a page before abandoning

props.name: cooldown
props.description: Cooldown between each fetch, only works if race is unset or false;

props.name: race
props.description: Issues simultaneous requests to the API, instead of requesting then parsing one by one. Can largely increase speed at the cost of hogging bandwidth and memory

props.name: includeItemBytes
props.description: Whether to include item bytes in the result
